Post title: Hide or remove 'Compose a Text Page' option
Post description: We've found that our faculty do not use the 'Compose a Text Page' option under Add a Resource. I would like to remove this option or hide it from the drop-down menu. Any help would be appreciated. Thanks! Lauren
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: login as Admin of your moodle, try looking under "Modules/ Activities ". It's probably there
Comment 2: Greetings, Lauren! I think this is a very good question ( asked before , but not answered then), and I cannot find an easy answer! I located this old thread (2006). http://moodle.org/mod/forum/discuss.php?d=47565 To hide the text page resource from the dropdown menu, Samuli Karavaara suggests: In course/lib.php, function print_section_add_menus() I changed 
```text
 foreach ($resourceraw as $type => $name) {
 $resources["resource&amp;type=$type"] = $name;
 }
```
 to 
```text
 foreach ($resourceraw as $type => $name) {
 if ($type != "text") {
 $resources["resource&amp;type=$type"] = $name;
 }
 }
```
Comment 3: Additional information: This has been filed in the issue tracker as well as a proposed fix. See and vote for: http://tracker.moodle.org/browse/MDL-18868 atw
